r"><p><strong>Calculator Instructions</strong>: Use these calculators to de=
termine how many BSI pitchable units you need to hit your desired pitch rat=
e for the beer you=E2=80=99re brewing. Whether you=E2=80=99re using dry yea=
st, liquid cultures, harvested slurry, or building multi-step starters, thi=
s calculator helps ensure you=E2=80=99re pitching the right number of viabl=
e cells for your specific wort parameters and desired pitch rate.</p>
<p>Enter your batch size in BBLs, SG in =C2=B0Plato if calculating by gravi=
ty, and your desired pitch rate.</p>
<p>Example Calculation: If you want to pitch a total of 18 million cells/ml=
 enter =E2=80=9C18=E2=80=9D or if you want to pitch 750,000 cells/ml/=C2=B0=
P enter =E2=80=9C0.75=E2=80=9D. BSI recommends the following pitch rates:</=
p>
<ul>
<li>For <a href=3D"https://brewingscience.com/product-category/ale/">ales</=
a> with a SG &lt;16=C2=B0P pitch 0.75 to 1.0 million cells/ml/=C2=B0P.</li>
<li>For <a href=3D"https://brewingscience.com/product-category/lager/">lage=
rs</a> with a SG &lt;16=C2=B0P pitch 1.5 million cells/ml/=C2=B0P.</li>
<li>For ales and lagers with a SG &gt;16=C2=B0P add an additional 0.5 milli=
on cells/ml/=C2=B0P to the listed pitch rates.</li>
<li>These are general guidelines. Optimal pitch rates can vary by beer styl=
e, fermentation temperature, yeast strain selection, and other variables.</=
li>
</ul>
